  "doc_id": "7534",
  "text": "All analyses were performed using intent-to-treat principles. Baseline characteristics were compared between groups with the use of 2 tests for categorical variables and analysis of variance for continuous variables. Mixed effects linear regression models were used to examine change in cognitive scores as a function of randomization group, time (baseline or postintervention), and the group ϫ time interaction. [CITATION_1] Random intercepts for each participant were used to model correlation between participants over time. Robust estimation of the variance-covariance structure was used to account for the possibility of unequal variance at the 2 time points. Because of the factorial design, analyses were performed to compare MA-I vs MA-C (ignoring exercise) and EX-I vs EX-C (ignoring mental activity), as well as all 4 randomization groups. Analyses were performed using the xtreg command in Stata 12 software (StataCorp).",
